WEBVTT

00:05.000 --> 00:06.800
How am I feeling? I'm a bit stressed.

00:06.880 --> 00:09.120
It's like, I never get stage anxiety.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.800
But because this is a new format,
new concept,

00:11.880 --> 00:14.520
new for me, stand-up comedy, like…

00:14.720 --> 00:17.640
compelled to be funny,
make sure the jokes land.

00:18.000 --> 00:19.320
There's like, high pressure.

00:19.400 --> 00:22.600
And I know that Sumukhi and Sapan have
worked really hard with me.

00:22.760 --> 00:24.520
I feel obligated to perform for them.

00:24.800 --> 00:25.880
More than anything else.

00:26.080 --> 00:28.760
I'm just afraid that I'll crack a joke
and no one will laugh.

00:28.840 --> 00:30.880
What am I afraid of?
That's what I'm afraid of.

01:07.320 --> 01:08.560
Hi, I'm your host and

01:08.640 --> 01:10.720
part-time sleep enthusiast, Sapan Verma.

01:10.920 --> 01:12.520
And on today's episode, we have

01:12.560 --> 01:14.920
the ever so charming
and disarmingly honest

01:15.000 --> 01:15.800
Karan Johar.

01:15.880 --> 01:18.920
And bringing out his funny side
is a comedian, writer,

01:19.040 --> 01:21.280
and everyone's favorite
on-screen stalker,

01:21.360 --> 01:22.280
Sumukhi Suresh.

01:22.360 --> 01:24.040
Good evening, guys!
I know you guys are like, "Wow!

01:24.120 --> 01:26.360
Sumukhi's dressed as Badshah today. Wow!"

01:27.080 --> 01:29.160
It's your boy Badshah!

01:31.000 --> 01:32.960
You guys are not allowed
to carry your bags, no?

01:34.720 --> 01:36.000
Look at the girls, they're like…

01:37.160 --> 01:38.800
Girls carry huge bags.

01:39.280 --> 01:40.200
Just giant bags.

01:40.280 --> 01:42.040
Like my bag, you should see,
it's bigger than me.

01:43.200 --> 01:44.600
And it's out of choice.

01:45.160 --> 01:46.920
I look for plus-size bags also.

01:48.120 --> 01:50.040
The reason I do that is
not because we're only shallow.

01:50.120 --> 01:51.000
Because we are.

01:51.680 --> 01:52.640
Even the small-bag girls.

01:52.720 --> 01:55.040
I'm very sure that small-bag girl
has a big bag in the car.

01:55.960 --> 01:58.760
Where she's like, "Small bag,
take it from the big bag, come…"

02:02.120 --> 02:03.920
We don't casually fling it around.

02:04.000 --> 02:05.520
We just hold onto it like this.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.800
The other thing big bags do
is that it hides something

02:09.880 --> 02:12.080
that just breaks the illusion
of a lot of things.

02:12.200 --> 02:13.360
See, you have big boobs, cool!

02:13.960 --> 02:14.880
You have a big ass, fine.

02:15.520 --> 02:17.600
Everyone's like "Wow, wow, wow!
Sexual, sexual, sexual!"

02:18.000 --> 02:19.320
But if you have a tummy, no!

02:20.240 --> 02:22.600
Because tummy breaks the illusion
of the fact that you're eating.

02:23.040 --> 02:25.160
And nobody wants to know that
you're eating.

02:25.240 --> 02:26.680
This is across sizes.

02:26.960 --> 02:28.960
Even if you have this one tiny…

02:29.160 --> 02:31.160
These thin people go saying,
"I have such a tummy…"

02:31.280 --> 02:32.840
I say, "I'll freaking slap you!"

02:34.560 --> 02:35.840
Even before going to restaurants,

02:35.880 --> 02:37.440
the first thing I check is not the menu.

02:37.720 --> 02:39.600
First thing I check is
"Do you have cushions?"

02:40.280 --> 02:41.280
And house parties…

02:41.360 --> 02:42.440
See, house parties is…

02:43.080 --> 02:44.760
for anxious people, whatever, whatever.

02:44.840 --> 02:46.440
You guys have your own shit going on.
God freaking knows.

02:46.520 --> 02:47.760
I'm very extrovert, man.

02:47.840 --> 02:49.160
So, I want to go also,
but I also have a tummy,

02:49.240 --> 02:50.200
so how to do this?

02:50.800 --> 02:52.840
So, I can't call them and be like,
"What kind of furniture do you have?"

02:54.000 --> 02:56.120
Especially this skinny-people furniture
is very skinny-people furniture.

02:56.200 --> 02:57.000
It's very like…

02:58.240 --> 03:01.200
Or they're like, "I'm sitting on
top of this, and what about that?"

03:02.120 --> 03:04.800
And I am just waiting,
and entering, I come early,

03:04.880 --> 03:08.480
so that the couch is empty
and I can take that

03:08.560 --> 03:09.840
cushion and just sit here.

03:10.240 --> 03:14.040
And my freaking luck, I'll go and
the thinnest bitch will be sitting there.

03:15.680 --> 03:17.120
Holding that cushion, she's like,
"I'm so comfortable."

03:17.200 --> 03:18.280
I'm like, "Of course, you are!

03:19.320 --> 03:21.280
You've got those biscuit abs
going on for yourself!"

03:26.440 --> 03:28.880
I wanna ask you, how many of
you guys are into casual sex here?

03:30.400 --> 03:31.680
See, it's one of those questions.

03:32.480 --> 03:33.720
Where they're like, "Sister, it's casual,

03:33.800 --> 03:35.640
which is why we're not talking about it."

03:37.200 --> 03:38.480
No, this casual sex is a huge thing, no?

03:38.560 --> 03:41.120
'Cause everyone is telling me,
"Sumukhi, after breakup, try casual."

03:41.560 --> 03:43.800
I said, "Why the hell are they
trying casual sex in India?"

03:43.880 --> 03:46.160
And why are girls behaving
like they're okay with casual?

03:46.240 --> 03:48.320
You know you've been trained
to look for <i>Sindoor.</i>

03:48.520 --> 03:49.600
Freaking look for it.

03:55.880 --> 03:58.160
We're not able to manage
the bag being down,

03:58.240 --> 03:59.880
you think we'll be managing casual?

04:02.200 --> 04:04.200
These girls are like, "No, I'm fine.
He can sleep with other girls."

04:04.280 --> 04:05.720
Sister, please look into your eyes.

04:05.920 --> 04:08.160
You will see,
you are irritated with him.

04:09.280 --> 04:11.200
And these boys also-- Come on!

04:11.400 --> 04:12.200
Come on!

04:12.560 --> 04:15.960
Boys can't even handle
a multi-cuisine order at a restaurant…

04:17.400 --> 04:19.240
if you tell them to order.
Yeah!

04:21.560 --> 04:22.720
At restaurants, they go, they're like,

04:22.800 --> 04:23.880
"Oh, no! There are
five Paneer dishes, bro.

04:23.920 --> 04:25.760
-What do you wanna order?'"
-"Bro, you order."

04:25.800 --> 04:27.600
-"But what do you…"
-"Please, you order, bro."

04:27.680 --> 04:29.240
-"Bro, Paneer…"
-"Bro, just do it."

04:34.560 --> 04:37.520
They can't differentiate
two Paneer dishes.

04:37.600 --> 04:39.320
How will you get these
idiots to do casual?

04:40.000 --> 04:42.080
Just tell them, "I'll sleep
with you for five days.

04:42.160 --> 04:44.480
If I don't see <i>Sindoor</i> after that,
I'll call your mom."

04:50.480 --> 04:52.520
Actually, that's all I wanted to say.

04:53.560 --> 04:54.360
This is just a PSA.

04:54.520 --> 04:56.920
Girls, stop trying to be casual
'cause you can't do it.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.880
Boys, just come on.
Accept the ultimatum.

04:59.360 --> 05:00.560
Because you're also getting that thing.

05:00.680 --> 05:02.120
Boys are also trained to think like,

05:02.200 --> 05:04.520
"She'll push me in a corner.
Then she'll get me married."

05:04.600 --> 05:06.120
And then they'll do
what they like the most.

05:06.200 --> 05:07.040
Complain.

05:08.600 --> 05:09.720
After they get married, they're like,

05:09.800 --> 05:11.880
"Marriage is a trap that a girl sets.

05:12.360 --> 05:13.360
Marriage is a trap.

05:13.480 --> 05:15.560
After that,
the girl goes clap, clap, clap."

05:17.000 --> 05:18.240
That's my time, guys.

05:18.320 --> 05:20.720
Thank you so much!
You guys have been a lovely audience.

05:29.760 --> 05:31.800
-Thank you so much for doing this.
-Oh, God!

05:32.440 --> 05:35.480
Did I just put myself into
lots of trouble by saying yes?

05:35.560 --> 05:36.840
-Always.
-Always.

05:37.120 --> 05:38.480
I always do that. I always do.

05:38.560 --> 05:41.280
I don't know how I land up
in trouble all the time.

05:41.480 --> 05:43.320
How did you say yes to this?
Like, who convinced you--

05:43.400 --> 05:44.440
You're gorgeous!

05:44.800 --> 05:46.640
-Oh, thank you! That's all I wanted.
-Are you crazy?

05:46.720 --> 05:48.440
-I thought it's a separate topic.
-That's all I wanted!

05:48.520 --> 05:50.680
Your drop-dead gorgeous
good looks got me here.

05:50.800 --> 05:53.720
-I think we're done for the day.
-And Sumukhi's high fashion.

05:53.800 --> 05:56.200
-Haven't you seen what she's worn today?
-Thank you, guys!

05:56.280 --> 05:57.760
It's a color-blocked layered cake.

05:57.840 --> 05:59.200
That's from Santacruz!

06:00.200 --> 06:01.160
Okay…

06:01.640 --> 06:02.520
That perhaps…

06:03.240 --> 06:04.400
But you look lovely!

06:04.560 --> 06:05.680
And I love the way you carry yourself.

06:05.880 --> 06:07.120
-I truly am a fan!
-Thank you!

06:07.200 --> 06:10.040
So, that's why I really need the
help of your humor device.

06:10.240 --> 06:11.480
-So, what do we do, how do we…
-No, that's fine.

06:11.600 --> 06:12.520
What do we-- I mean…

06:12.640 --> 06:14.080
It'll be great if we get to see…

06:14.200 --> 06:16.880
Everybody knows the film angle,

06:16.960 --> 06:17.960
-Yeah.
-and the director angle.

06:18.040 --> 06:19.640
-But the personal stuff.
-Yeah!

06:19.720 --> 06:21.040
-The personal stuff.
-Especially like…

06:21.120 --> 06:22.440
some of the anecdotes
that you've mentioned

06:22.520 --> 06:24.080
where you know, the fact that…

06:24.160 --> 06:25.160
Your whole mid--

06:25.240 --> 06:26.400
The mid-life crisis angle.

06:26.480 --> 06:28.120
Or something else.
It'd be very interesting to…

06:28.280 --> 06:29.560
And I <i>am</i> going through it.

06:29.640 --> 06:31.760
Okay. So what is going on in the
mid-life crisis right now?

06:31.840 --> 06:32.800
What are the things you are feeling?

06:33.120 --> 06:34.600
Inappropriate fashion would be one.

06:34.680 --> 06:35.760
-Yeah.
-Like, mid-life…

06:35.840 --> 06:38.880
Second is, wanting to hang
with people half my age.

06:39.440 --> 06:41.040
-Yeah. Okay.
-It's reached that point,

06:41.240 --> 06:42.920
where I'm like, "Hey, what are
you guys doing?" and

06:43.000 --> 06:44.600
they're like, in their head bubble, like,

06:44.800 --> 06:48.120
"Nothing, uncle. Stay away!
Stay away. Stay out of my zone."

06:48.200 --> 06:51.920
The third is, recently,
I'm really trying hard to

06:52.000 --> 06:57.080
break through the pop culture of the
millennial and the Gen-Z generation.

06:57.160 --> 06:59.880
Tell me something. You're surrounding
yourself with so many young people.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.600
Are they really candid
and honest with you?

07:01.680 --> 07:04.040
I actually have the
opposite effect on people.

07:04.120 --> 07:06.520
For some reason, they feel
very obliged to be honest to me.

07:06.880 --> 07:10.480
Especially when I did that anthology
with Zoya, Dibakar, Anurag…

07:10.560 --> 07:12.840
I really felt like, you know…
And I really said,

07:13.200 --> 07:14.520
"I'm gonna do this anthology.

07:14.600 --> 07:15.760
I'm gonna start with Bombay Talkies

07:15.840 --> 07:18.360
because I really want that critics' nod."

07:18.440 --> 07:19.560
-I want it!
-Yeah.

07:19.760 --> 07:22.240
I wanted that community
to say that I can do it.

07:22.320 --> 07:24.920
So, I took close-ups of a lot of things.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.240
-Like this.
-These props.

07:26.320 --> 07:27.160
I swear, the props.

07:27.240 --> 07:28.200
In complete silence…

07:29.240 --> 07:30.720
So, they'd say it is "atmospheric".

07:30.880 --> 07:34.560
Then I'd take a long shot so
they'd say that it has a perspective.

07:34.640 --> 07:35.960
I made the characters enter slowly.

07:36.040 --> 07:37.240
-Mise-en-scène!
-I did a lot of things.

07:37.320 --> 07:39.360
I chose a sensational topic.

07:39.440 --> 07:41.160
I did everything, and…

07:41.240 --> 07:43.320
then it was like,
"Surprisingly, Karan Johar's film…"

07:43.400 --> 07:44.400
I was like…

07:44.520 --> 07:47.360
I never get praise from the
industry, I don't know why.

07:47.440 --> 07:49.080
Something about me irritates people.

07:49.880 --> 07:50.840
I don't know what it is.

07:50.920 --> 07:52.600
I think it's maybe
because I'm like potatoes,

07:52.680 --> 07:55.400
you put me everywhere,
and it somehow fits.

07:56.000 --> 07:57.640
I'm the potatoes of this industry.

07:57.840 --> 07:59.440
When people narrate comedy movies,

07:59.520 --> 08:00.960
are you a huge laugher?

08:01.040 --> 08:01.840
No, I don't laugh.

08:01.920 --> 08:03.000
-Oh, my God!
-Man!

08:03.080 --> 08:05.240
I don't know, I'm not…
So, I was gonna say that to you guys.

08:05.320 --> 08:06.960
I always tell people to
narrate comedies to me.

08:07.040 --> 08:08.680
And like, I'm laughing in my head.

08:08.760 --> 08:11.120
-That's the worst kind!
-No, Karan, don't do that to us!

08:11.200 --> 08:12.040
Don't do that.

08:12.120 --> 08:13.920
What is the strangest or funniest
narration you've had?

08:14.040 --> 08:16.040
-Yeah, the comedy narration, I don't know.
-The weird one.

08:16.120 --> 08:18.280
Oh, there was a director.
I won't mention his name.

08:18.480 --> 08:22.000
Very quiet, dignified,
soft-spoken gentleman.

08:22.400 --> 08:23.760
Had a sip of his water.

08:24.280 --> 08:26.120
And I was also, you know, like that.

08:26.200 --> 08:27.120
Suddenly, he just got up.

08:27.600 --> 08:28.880
That's when I was like…

08:30.080 --> 08:31.760
He began like
that and I was like…

08:31.840 --> 08:34.200
When he said, "We begin with a…"
and then he stood up.

08:34.280 --> 08:35.280
And he started going…

08:35.360 --> 08:37.440
He performed action on his own,

08:37.520 --> 08:39.160
-emotion, he started crying,
-God!

08:39.240 --> 08:41.240
he threw the chair
in the middle of an action.

08:41.320 --> 08:43.400
I was like, "He's going to hit me!

08:43.480 --> 08:44.840
He's going to kill me!

08:44.880 --> 08:46.720
I will not survive this narration."

08:46.840 --> 08:48.880
It didn't give me any sign.

08:49.120 --> 08:50.280
But okay apart from narration,

08:50.360 --> 08:51.880
who do you think is a
funny person in Bollywood?

08:52.000 --> 08:52.960
Who'd be good at stand-up?

08:53.040 --> 08:54.320
-Apart from…
-Javed Akhtar!

08:54.440 --> 08:56.080
-Javed Akhtar would be…
-He's hilarious!

08:56.160 --> 08:57.880
He told me once about Shabana.

08:58.520 --> 08:59.440
And very, like…

08:59.520 --> 09:02.280
He said, "Every time you tell
Shabana a joke, she tries to solve it."

09:06.080 --> 09:08.600
So, when you said who's the
funniest man in the fraternity,

09:08.640 --> 09:11.880
I'd say, undoubtedly Javed Akhtar.
and then Shahrukh Khan.

09:12.120 --> 09:13.840
-Of course.
-Shahrukh is hilarious!

09:13.880 --> 09:16.000
-He's too funny.
-His comedy is for like…

09:16.440 --> 09:18.480
-Like, a far more evolved audience.
-Evolved audience.

09:18.520 --> 09:20.360
Because people should be
able to take a joke at themselves.

09:20.440 --> 09:21.240
-Like I can.
-Yes!

09:21.320 --> 09:23.040
Who have you told that
you're doing stand-up?

09:23.200 --> 09:24.760
-Have you told anyone?
-No, not really.

09:24.840 --> 09:26.200
-Have you told your mom?
-Yeah!

09:26.280 --> 09:29.240
She already said that
"The things you do today…"

09:29.320 --> 09:31.360
and just shut the door on my face.

09:31.520 --> 09:33.440
I think it's a great omen, I must say.

09:33.520 --> 09:34.440
-It's like a great sign.
-Yeah, she was--

09:34.520 --> 09:37.400
I didn't get any good
wishes this morning, let me tell you!

09:37.480 --> 09:40.240
-I got like, "The things you do!"
-She just cursed you!

09:40.320 --> 09:43.120
And she just gave me that
Meryl Streep from <i>Devil Wears Prada</i> look

09:43.200 --> 09:44.080
and I had to…

09:44.160 --> 09:45.280
I get that from her all the time.

09:45.360 --> 09:47.000
That's all I get all the time.

09:47.080 --> 09:48.160
What do you really want to tell him?

09:48.240 --> 09:49.640
At any given point on stage,

09:49.880 --> 09:51.760
the most powerful person on
that stage is you.

09:51.840 --> 09:52.720
Has to be you.

09:52.760 --> 09:55.360
-So, maintain that power. Be like, okay.
-So, create that power energy.

09:55.440 --> 09:57.120
Yeah, but if you have
a little bit of sass,

09:57.200 --> 09:59.480
like, a good amount of…
20% sass has to be there.

09:59.720 --> 10:01.160
Where they're like,
"Okay, he's laughing at himself,

10:01.240 --> 10:02.440
but he can laugh at me too."

10:02.520 --> 10:03.440
If someone doesn't laugh,

10:03.520 --> 10:04.840
he's gonna be like,
"Why didn't you laugh?"

10:04.880 --> 10:06.240
I think you'll be amazing.

10:06.320 --> 10:07.840
I've seen and survived failure, madam.

10:08.600 --> 10:10.880
-I know what it feels like.
-That's too dramatic!

10:10.960 --> 10:11.840
One tear falling…

10:12.080 --> 10:13.640
It's <i>Karan ke Khayal</i>, come on.
It has to be.

10:13.720 --> 10:15.000
Oh! <i>Karan ke Khayal!</i>

10:15.120 --> 10:16.440
Okay, that's about me.

10:16.520 --> 10:17.720
But what do we do about you guys?

10:17.760 --> 10:19.520
You said power on stage,
like you've taught me,

10:19.600 --> 10:21.160
I wanna teach you fashion power.

10:21.240 --> 10:22.480
So, you'll teach us this in role reversal.

10:22.520 --> 10:23.880
Yeah, I mean I'll try.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.400
Because I don't promise success.

10:27.080 --> 10:29.520
'Cause raw material is very essential
and I don't have any.

10:29.600 --> 10:31.640
-Neither do we on stand-up, Karan.
-Hey, man!

10:32.400 --> 10:33.200
High-five!

10:33.400 --> 10:34.600
High-five! Savage!

10:34.640 --> 10:36.120
You're like my mom. I love it.

10:37.200 --> 10:38.880
-Sapan is actually--
-I'm gonna call you Hiroo.

10:41.200 --> 10:42.480
-Shall we go?
-Let's do it.

10:42.520 --> 10:43.760
-Okay, come. Let's go.
-Yeah, let's go.

10:47.640 --> 10:49.520
We have a rack full of clothes for you.

10:50.040 --> 10:52.960
So, I wanted to tell you that by mistake,

10:53.040 --> 10:55.400
he's stumbled into a very popular print.

10:55.480 --> 10:56.520
It's not by mistake, alright?

10:57.000 --> 10:58.360
-Really, you knew or what?
-I did research.

10:58.480 --> 11:00.040
-You did research? Alright.
-Yeah.

11:00.520 --> 11:01.880
Okay, we'll get into that later.

11:01.960 --> 11:03.840
And I wonder what that research was.

11:03.920 --> 11:06.880
Because it's tie-dye, I want to
make you wear something that I love…

11:06.960 --> 11:07.800
Okay.

11:07.880 --> 11:10.720
It's a red tie-dye.

11:10.920 --> 11:11.760
Voila!

11:15.360 --> 11:17.720
Which is your better profile?
