-What's your better profile?
-You tell me.

11:55.320 --> 11:56.120
Is it left?

11:57.160 --> 11:59.440
Just walk straight.
You don't have a profile.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.120
-Alright, let's do it. Walk the talk.
-Yeah!

12:04.120 --> 12:04.920
-Stop.
-Stop.

12:05.320 --> 12:06.160
Pose.

12:07.840 --> 12:08.680
Profiles.

12:10.040 --> 12:12.040
-Sumukhi, get your act together.
-Yeah. Okay.

12:12.880 --> 12:15.040
We're done. Clap, clap.
Applause, applause.

12:15.120 --> 12:17.600
I'm semi-stressed, but
I know you guys are there.

12:17.840 --> 12:20.360
You're gonna be great.
You just have to be yourself.

12:20.520 --> 12:21.560
-Okay.
-With lines.

12:21.640 --> 12:23.400
Yeah, my problem is when I'm myself.

12:24.240 --> 12:25.720
Let's do this. Let's practice,
let's write some jokes.

12:25.800 --> 12:27.040
-Yeah.
-We'll see you over the weekend.

12:27.120 --> 12:28.960
-Alright. Thank you, guys!
-Okay! Thank you!

12:37.040 --> 12:40.120
I woke up and then I was like,
"Oh, God, I have this thing to do!"

12:40.360 --> 12:43.440
And then I got a very rare feeling.

12:43.640 --> 12:45.960
It was called anxiety of stage.

12:46.040 --> 12:47.560
Which I don't normally get.

12:47.640 --> 12:50.400
I got a little scared,
nervous, anxious and then…

12:50.840 --> 12:52.920
I closed my eyes and I imagined

12:53.240 --> 12:56.600
both of your wonderful, supportive faces.

12:56.720 --> 12:57.640
Thank God you said that.

12:57.720 --> 13:00.640
-Then I got so scared, after that!
-There it is.

13:00.840 --> 13:02.600
Any instructions?

13:02.680 --> 13:03.520
Thank you!

13:04.080 --> 13:06.320
-It's too…
-I think this is exactly what it is.

13:06.400 --> 13:07.200
Hold your power.

13:07.400 --> 13:09.360
I'm telling you, half your job is done.

13:09.440 --> 13:11.200
On stage, go self-deprecating but…

13:11.280 --> 13:13.160
-How long do I hold this power?
-No, no, no.

13:13.360 --> 13:15.480
I am tired of holding this power.

13:15.560 --> 13:17.040
When will it let go of me?

13:17.120 --> 13:18.040
Just one more night, sir.

13:18.120 --> 13:20.120
Then you can do what you want.

13:20.200 --> 13:21.040
Let's do a soundcheck.

13:21.120 --> 13:22.560
-We'll take you through the stage.
-Okay.

13:22.640 --> 13:23.720
Or you don't want to do that also?

13:23.800 --> 13:26.520
No, no, no. Are you cray-cray-cray?

13:26.760 --> 13:28.440
-I'm a stage baby.
-Stage baby!

13:28.520 --> 13:31.240
You think Mom and Dad will have
to hold my hand and carry me?

13:41.360 --> 13:44.520
Hello, hello!
God, you guys all showed up!

13:44.600 --> 13:47.680
Especially these two rows
would want eye contact from you.

13:47.760 --> 13:49.400
I know exactly what I was doing wrong.

13:49.480 --> 13:51.000
So, I won't let that happen.

13:51.080 --> 13:52.760
I think in the tech check, he was already

13:52.840 --> 13:54.160
-improvising a lot of jokes.
-Yeah.

13:54.320 --> 13:59.320
So, I hope he's in that zone
where he still does it uninhibitedly.

13:59.440 --> 14:01.640
So, this is my charity for the year.

14:01.720 --> 14:02.520
Okay.

14:02.600 --> 14:04.120
Who'll be the proudest seeing me perform?

14:04.200 --> 14:05.680
I think both my stage parents.

14:05.760 --> 14:07.440
My stage mummy and my stage daddy.

14:07.520 --> 14:10.960
They made me their
self-appointed stage baby, so

14:11.040 --> 14:12.640
I think they'll be the
proudest. Hopefully.

14:12.720 --> 14:13.880
He's not trying to be anything else.

14:13.960 --> 14:16.600
He's like, "This is me and
I'm going to improvise in my space."

14:16.680 --> 14:18.200
So, I think that's best.

14:19.280 --> 14:22.920
If tonight doesn't go well,
just look into the camera and say,

14:23.000 --> 14:25.600
<i>"Accha chalta hoon,</i>
<i>dua mein yaad rakhna…"</i>

14:34.800 --> 14:36.600
Have you guys noticed,
in the last two or three years,

14:36.680 --> 14:40.040
a lot of these multiplexes
have launched luxury theaters.

14:40.440 --> 14:42.400
One ticket for 1500 bucks.

14:43.280 --> 14:45.720
I paid. I wanted to see
what is this experience.

14:46.200 --> 14:47.600
I went inside. The minute you enter,

14:47.680 --> 14:49.680
there are like business class
reclining sofa seats.

14:50.360 --> 14:53.440
The minute you enter,
they hand you a pillow, a blanket.

14:53.880 --> 14:56.200
I'm like, "Bro, do you want me
to watch the movie or not?"

14:56.960 --> 14:58.000
What the hell?

14:58.080 --> 15:00.440
If you add one Medimix soap,
this will become an OYO room.

15:01.680 --> 15:02.640
That's where we are.

15:03.160 --> 15:04.040
What's the point?

15:06.880 --> 15:09.520
They don't even have normal food.
They have posh food now.

15:10.280 --> 15:12.160
Normally, you get samosas,
nachos and all. No!

15:12.240 --> 15:14.880
This is what they had on their menu.
They had Avocado Toast,

15:15.440 --> 15:17.080
Char-grilled Chicken Steak,

15:17.360 --> 15:19.040
California Sushi Roll.

15:19.880 --> 15:21.760
So posh! I think the
next thing they will say is,

15:21.840 --> 15:22.960
"Stag entry not allowed."

15:25.120 --> 15:25.920
There's a popcorn stall.

15:26.000 --> 15:27.120
I was like, finally, there's popcorn.

15:27.200 --> 15:28.520
I went there, I'm like, "Hi,
can I have some popcorn?"

15:28.600 --> 15:31.240
The guy was like,
"Sir, we have gourmet popcorn."

15:32.080 --> 15:33.920
I was like, 'No, I don't want
'ghur-me' (at home), I want it here.'

15:35.520 --> 15:36.400
Right now.

15:36.760 --> 15:38.120
I have popcorn at home.

15:39.320 --> 15:41.960
He was like, "No chance you're
getting popcorn after such a bad joke!"

15:43.200 --> 15:45.560
I know at some point, all of us have tried

15:45.640 --> 15:47.720
sneaking food into a multiplex.

15:48.200 --> 15:49.320
We've all done that, right?

15:49.560 --> 15:51.120
But there's that security guard outside.

15:51.200 --> 15:52.240
Have you seen that guy?

15:52.600 --> 15:54.040
That guy is a genius, dude!

15:54.520 --> 15:56.080
Place him on the national border.

15:56.880 --> 15:59.200
He manages to find food from
anywhere inside the bag.

15:59.800 --> 16:01.840
I took chips inside a laptop sleeve.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.200
He took that out, dude.

16:03.600 --> 16:04.720
Last time I went, he was like,

16:04.800 --> 16:07.400
"Sir, you have food stuck in your teeth.
Outside food not allowed."

16:08.400 --> 16:10.200
I'm like, "Are you a dentist too?
What's going on?"

16:11.120 --> 16:11.960
And I read this recently.

16:12.040 --> 16:15.000
Somebody has made this
online petition saying,

16:15.080 --> 16:18.320
"We should be allowed to carry
our own food inside theaters."

16:18.720 --> 16:19.720
But please…

16:20.600 --> 16:21.880
do not sign this shit.

16:22.720 --> 16:25.080
Because let me remind you
that we are Indians.

16:26.200 --> 16:27.640
Once you give us this liberty,

16:29.000 --> 16:29.920
we will not use it.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.080
We will exploit the shit out of it!

16:33.040 --> 16:35.120
Right? We'll carry anything inside.

16:35.440 --> 16:38.320
Forget popcorn, we'll carry corn
and a microwave oven inside.

16:39.640 --> 16:42.400
Right? And we'll be like,
"We will make popcorn right here."

16:45.520 --> 16:46.520
Alright.

16:47.560 --> 16:48.360
So…

16:48.800 --> 16:51.840
Usually, this man is the
one who's responsible

16:51.920 --> 16:53.800
for launching new talent into Bollywood.

16:54.960 --> 16:57.840
But tonight, we're launching him
into the world of stand-up comedy.

16:58.400 --> 16:59.520
So, ladies and gents, come on.

16:59.600 --> 17:02.040
Start clapping and cheering
and please welcome to the stage…

17:02.400 --> 17:05.160
Karan Johar!

17:17.920 --> 17:19.080
Oh, my God!

17:24.680 --> 17:26.200
God, so many of you showed up!

17:27.680 --> 17:29.200
Not that I need any introduction.

17:30.000 --> 17:31.400
But I am Karan Johar.

17:31.560 --> 17:33.560
I'm a producer, I'm a director.

17:33.800 --> 17:34.800
I'm a host.

17:34.920 --> 17:36.680
I'm also the man responsible for

17:36.760 --> 17:38.960
setting unrealistic standards in college.

17:44.200 --> 17:45.720
So, people keep saying,

17:45.800 --> 17:48.560
"Karan, you only launch privileged people

17:48.800 --> 17:51.280
who would become superstars anyway.

17:51.320 --> 17:54.800
Why don't you launch somebody
who has no chance at stardom?

17:54.920 --> 17:56.560
Nothing! Absolutely nothing!"

17:56.800 --> 17:57.800
Then Sapan called.

18:01.880 --> 18:04.200
I've been in the industry only… what?

18:04.280 --> 18:05.160
23 years.

18:05.240 --> 18:07.960
So, naturally, when a fan comes up to me,

18:08.240 --> 18:10.000
what is he or she meant to tell me, right?

18:10.080 --> 18:11.320
They come up to me and they say,

18:11.440 --> 18:12.720
"What's in the hamper?"

18:14.160 --> 18:16.800
I'm like, "Dude! I have a career!

18:17.000 --> 18:18.880
It stretches nearly 25 years.

18:18.960 --> 18:20.960
You want to know what's in
my freaking coffee hamper?"

18:21.760 --> 18:23.480
That's the legacy I've left behind.

18:23.560 --> 18:24.680
Freaking coffee.

18:27.400 --> 18:28.560
It hurts!

18:28.760 --> 18:30.720
I'm turning 50.
I know I don't look it!

18:32.160 --> 18:33.320
Thank you!

18:34.080 --> 18:36.000
I'm really struggling though.

18:36.080 --> 18:37.760
To be not out of touch.

18:37.800 --> 18:38.880
You know when you wanna be

18:38.960 --> 18:41.520
with the Gen-Zs and
the millennial generations?

18:41.880 --> 18:44.680
It's my self-aware mid-life crisis.

18:45.240 --> 18:48.280
So, the other day,
a teenager came up to me and said that

18:48.560 --> 18:50.160
"I love K-dramas!"

18:50.240 --> 18:52.640
I said, "Which one?
<i>K3G</i> or <i>Kuch Kuch Hota Hai?"</i>

18:54.040 --> 18:56.960
Then they gave me such a blank,
straight-face look and I said

18:57.280 --> 18:59.080
"Sorry, man. I didn't know
you were talking about

18:59.160 --> 19:02.200
<i>Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi</i>
and <i>Kasauti Zindagi Ki."</i>

19:03.800 --> 19:05.720
Then the K 'pop'ped in my head!

19:06.480 --> 19:09.720
Okay. Even my clothes have become
more Gen-Z, as you can see.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.080
Like, double chain.

19:11.760 --> 19:12.720
That's the way…

19:12.800 --> 19:13.560
<i>Mahi way!</i>

19:13.800 --> 19:14.560
Anyway…

19:16.560 --> 19:19.080
In fact, I love flaunting
my clothes so much

19:19.200 --> 19:20.800
sometimes I drive to the airport.

19:20.920 --> 19:23.200
Literally, drive to
the airport just to get papped.

19:24.240 --> 19:26.040
Now, you know that
we pay the paps, you know.

19:26.080 --> 19:28.520
And then we all pretend when we
come out and there are cameras,

19:28.560 --> 19:30.800
like "Oh, they're here!
How do they find out?"

19:31.040 --> 19:32.000
We paid you!

19:32.520 --> 19:33.560
That's why you're here.

19:34.560 --> 19:36.320
I know, I'm privileged.

19:37.440 --> 19:38.640
I grew up in Malabar Hill.

19:38.720 --> 19:40.880
I love Almond Milk, Avocado Smoothie,

19:40.960 --> 19:43.240
my shoes cost more than
the budget of <i>Kalank.</i>

19:45.480 --> 19:46.880
Should've stuck to my shoes.

19:48.920 --> 19:50.800
But I've had my own struggles, guys.

19:50.920 --> 19:51.800
I've had.

19:52.080 --> 19:53.720
It pains me to say this, but…

19:53.960 --> 19:55.080
I've struggled.

19:56.320 --> 19:57.920
I'm gonna take a moment because…

19:58.320 --> 20:00.040
it's reminded me of my struggles.

20:02.440 --> 20:03.640
Yeah, just…

20:10.080 --> 20:11.280
I'll do a "Tabu".

20:14.800 --> 20:16.440
I'm a struggling actor.

20:17.720 --> 20:19.400
And now with my mid-life crisis,

20:19.480 --> 20:22.240
I'm getting desperate to
go pursue my Bollywood dream.

20:22.560 --> 20:25.320
I'm a man in Bollywood who's almost 50.

20:25.440 --> 20:27.440
So, obviously, roles are limited, right?

20:27.760 --> 20:31.040
I mean I know I could play a
college boy for just five years more.

20:32.080 --> 20:33.440
I mean, it's hard.

20:35.080 --> 20:37.280
I did a film, by the way.
I did a film.

20:37.320 --> 20:38.520
2015.

20:38.720 --> 20:40.520
It was called <i>Bombay Velvet.</i>

20:40.560 --> 20:43.200
Give me a cheer
if you saw <i>Bombay Velvet.</i>

20:44.520 --> 20:45.440
Shit!

20:47.080 --> 20:48.240
And it still flopped.

20:49.320 --> 20:51.440
Shit, that film wasn't received well
at all at the box office.

20:51.520 --> 20:52.760
It got thrashed.

20:52.960 --> 20:55.760
But you know what, I didn't even get
one single bad review. Not one.

20:56.080 --> 20:58.080
I genuinely think
I wasn't so bad in the film.

20:58.160 --> 21:00.080
I mean, not because
I'm speaking for myself,

21:00.160 --> 21:01.440
but I wasn't so bad.

21:01.720 --> 21:03.760
In fact, I think people loved me.

21:04.240 --> 21:05.280
They loved me!

21:06.000 --> 21:08.480
But it's been seven years since that day.

21:08.720 --> 21:09.720
Not a single offer.

21:10.760 --> 21:12.560
Not even a freaking bad one.

21:12.800 --> 21:13.880
I told Zoya Akhtar…

21:14.160 --> 21:15.080
You know, Zoya Akhtar.

21:15.960 --> 21:17.320
"Why don't you cast me in <i>Made in Heaven?</i>

21:17.760 --> 21:19.960
Rich people, rich weddings,
rich problems…

21:20.080 --> 21:20.920
Totally me!

21:21.000 --> 21:22.000
I can only see…

21:22.080 --> 21:23.680
That's the role that I was made for!"

21:24.200 --> 21:26.280
And she said she wants
to cast talented actors.

21:26.480 --> 21:27.400
Who does that?

21:30.320 --> 21:32.000
Who freaking casts talented actors?

21:32.880 --> 21:34.240
I don't know when I last did that.

21:34.880 --> 21:37.440
The only time I get to
really channel my inner actor

21:37.520 --> 21:38.720
is when I watch preview screenings.

21:38.800 --> 21:40.720
You know, when you go to
watch other directors' movies.

21:41.200 --> 21:43.160
And you've hated it, so you just say,

21:43.240 --> 21:45.520
"Man, I'm speechless!"

21:46.960 --> 21:47.760
Could mean anything.

21:48.160 --> 21:51.280
And they're like, "Really?"
I'm like, "Really speechless!"

21:52.080 --> 21:54.200
I thought the one benefit
of my mid-life crisis was

21:54.280 --> 21:56.920
actually that people would
give me some respect, though.

21:57.000 --> 21:58.440
I have to say. Some respect.

21:58.720 --> 22:00.800
Some little respect, not asking for much.

22:00.880 --> 22:04.120
But for some reason, everyone feels
comfortable being honest with me.

22:04.200 --> 22:06.280
Sometimes, too freaking honest!

22:07.120 --> 22:08.680
I don't have any "Yes-men".

22:08.760 --> 22:10.880
I have "Yes-you-really-suck-men".

22:11.960 --> 22:13.160
Okay, that came out all wrong.

22:20.840 --> 22:22.560
I mean, even if I do, it's legal.

22:24.160 --> 22:25.040
So…

22:31.520 --> 22:34.360
Mom, you're gonna watch this;
you're gonna kill me.

22:34.440 --> 22:36.520
I just know it, you know,

22:36.600 --> 22:38.240
this is-- This is not a roast.

22:38.320 --> 22:39.800
I'm just… This is a toast.

22:39.880 --> 22:41.760
A toast to you, a toast to everyone here.

22:42.400 --> 22:45.360
I don't know why people
who are so mean to me

22:45.440 --> 22:47.800
don't have the basic decency
and courtesy to

22:47.880 --> 22:49.760
bitch about me behind my back.

22:49.840 --> 22:50.640
Like I do.

22:51.640 --> 22:52.840
Why can't they just do that?

22:52.920 --> 22:55.840
I mean like, if you really
want to insult me to my face,

22:56.000 --> 22:57.400
just come on <i>Koffee with Karan!</i>

23:02.360 --> 23:05.400
The biggest sign of
my mid-life crisis is that

23:05.640 --> 23:07.600
I still live with my mummy.

23:08.600 --> 23:10.160
My mummy… My mummy.

23:10.400 --> 23:11.280
Oh, God!

23:11.480 --> 23:13.320
My mum is 79.

23:13.760 --> 23:15.920
She's ten years older
than my favorite thing.

23:22.360 --> 23:24.160
Online trolls don't bother me because

23:24.240 --> 23:26.560
my mum is my biggest troll.

23:27.360 --> 23:30.160
So, I was thinking about getting
botox done in the future.

23:30.240 --> 23:31.120
I really was.

23:31.840 --> 23:32.920
Not that I need it.

23:34.200 --> 23:35.120
You see?

23:36.000 --> 23:37.160
So, I asked my mom

23:37.240 --> 23:40.600
which part of my face
requires any fillers.

23:40.800 --> 23:41.720
She said, "Your face is fine.

23:41.800 --> 23:43.480
What about your scripts?
They need fillers."

23:47.680 --> 23:51.960
Yeah, of course, I agree my movies are
a little over the top.

23:52.280 --> 23:54.000
But realism is overrated, right? It is.

23:54.080 --> 23:55.160
It's totally overrated.

23:55.480 --> 23:59.480
Sometimes you need to believe that
if you are a plus-sized kid,

23:59.800 --> 24:01.400
and called Laddoo,

24:01.480 --> 24:03.720
you grow up and look like Hrithik Roshan.

24:04.360 --> 24:06.240
I mean, dude. Hrithik Roshan is hot!

24:06.320 --> 24:08.680
Didn't you love him
in the homo-erotic <i>War?</i>

24:09.880 --> 24:12.280
It's the first time I saw a freaking man

24:12.360 --> 24:14.680
get introduced and
only men were looking at him!

24:15.320 --> 24:17.280
Did you see Ashutosh Rana's face?

24:17.840 --> 24:20.000
He looked like he saw
Disha Patani on the beach.

24:20.880 --> 24:22.720
When all he did was see Hrithik Roshan

24:22.800 --> 24:24.440
coming out in slow motion.

24:24.520 --> 24:26.680
Hrithik looked drop-dead gorgeous!

24:26.760 --> 24:28.800
And even Tiger Shroff says, "Get in line."

24:28.880 --> 24:31.480
I'm like, I wanna be in that line, too.

24:32.680 --> 24:34.640
Duggu is the man to go to!

24:37.560 --> 24:38.960
People have exes.

24:39.040 --> 24:40.440
People have exes. We all do.

24:40.520 --> 24:42.280
I know I do, I'm sure all of you do.

24:42.360 --> 24:44.240
Unless you are an
ex yourself right now and…

24:44.600 --> 24:46.360
My apologies, <i>"Channa Mereya"</i> to you.

24:47.880 --> 24:50.040
People have exes who
come back in their lives.

24:50.400 --> 24:51.720
I have ex-movies!

24:51.920 --> 24:54.560
I can't watch my old stuff. I cringe.
I literally cringe.

24:54.640 --> 24:57.360
Even I can't watch the climax of
<i>Kuch Kuch Hota Hai,</i>

24:57.440 --> 24:59.240
where Rani walks like a ghost.

24:59.440 --> 25:02.760
She walks like a ghost as she
gets her ex-husband married.

25:02.960 --> 25:05.280
Poor thing! I made her
attend her ex's wedding.

25:06.200 --> 25:09.720
Dude, she named her daughter after
her husband's ex-best friend,

25:10.080 --> 25:11.440
who was in love with him!

25:11.560 --> 25:12.520
Who does that?

25:13.000 --> 25:16.000
It's like Angelina Jolie naming
her child Jennifer!

25:16.800 --> 25:17.720
Ain't gonna happen.

25:18.200 --> 25:20.440
It ain't gonna happen.
Only happens in Bollywood.

25:21.200 --> 25:22.560
It happens only in India.

25:23.920 --> 25:26.720
And this isn't me justifying
my earlier movies at all.

25:26.800 --> 25:29.600
But we learn, we grow over time, you know.
It takes a while.

25:29.680 --> 25:31.320
I'm sure we all have Facebook memories

25:31.440 --> 25:33.160
we're all completely embarrassed of!

25:33.480 --> 25:35.640
Who has really embarrassing
Facebook memories?

25:36.240 --> 25:39.440
Nobody? You're all gorgeous, beautiful
Aishwarya Rais here in the audience?

25:39.600 --> 25:40.440
Nobody?

25:41.520 --> 25:43.760
What a vain lot of people!

25:43.960 --> 25:45.480
Y'all actually think that y'all click

25:45.560 --> 25:47.600
really good photographs of yourselves?

25:47.720 --> 25:50.640
Just because you all are masked
doesn't mean I can't see!

25:55.240 --> 25:56.040
Anyway.

25:56.240 --> 25:57.560
I hope with all my heart

25:57.640 --> 25:59.360
that I haven't offended anyone of you.

25:59.440 --> 26:00.720
'Cause I don't want to go to jail.

26:00.840 --> 26:02.600
Though it seems everyone is there.

26:04.040 --> 26:05.160
It's like the new Maldives.

